Possible Questions And Answers

Q: Why did you use TF-IDF?
A: Because text must be converted into numbers before a machine learning model can use it. TF-IDF is simple, fast, and works well for small text classification projects.

Q: Why Logistic Regression?
A: It is beginner-friendly, efficient, works well with TF-IDF, supports multi-class classification, and gives confidence scores.

Q: Why use rules if you already have a model?
A: Rules improve explainability. If the word “predict” appears, we can clearly explain why the result is supervised learning.

Q: What is the limitation of this project?
A: The dataset is small, so the model may not generalize well to all real-world business problems. Adding more examples will improve it.

Q: What happens if there is no keyword?
A: The system uses only the Logistic Regression model prediction.

Q: Can this project be improved?
A: Yes. We can add more data, more keywords, better preprocessing, cross-validation, larger models, or save the trained model using joblib.

Q: Is this real AI or just rules?
A: It is both. The main prediction comes from a trained machine learning model, and the rule layer adds simple explainability and correction for obvious keywords.

Q: Why is accuracy not 100%?
A: Because the dataset is small and some descriptions can be ambiguous. In real ML, accuracy improves with more high-quality training data.

